body:
(1) The general assembly hereby finds, determines, and declares that the purposes of the Colorado Income Tax Act of 1987 include, but are not limited to:
(a) Simplifying the preparation of state income tax returns;
(b) Aiding in the interpretation of the state income tax law through increased
use of federal judicial and administrative determinations and precedents;
(c) Improving the enforcement of the state income tax laws through better
use of information obtained from federal income tax audits.
